## Initialization Procedure
Trigger: "initialize project" or first run when `.ai.dev/` is missing.

### Execution Order
```
Step 1. AGENT_CONFIG.md check
  → Missing: attempt model self-identification
           → Success: look up spec → create AGENT_CONFIG.md
           → Failure: ask user once → create AGENT_CONFIG.md
  → Exists: load and proceed to Step 2

Step 2. .ai.dev/ folder structure creation
  → Create .ai.dev/ if missing
  → Create DECISIONS.md
  → Create context/ folder for archives

Step 3. Project Questions (Q0~Q16)
  Ask in groups. NEVER ask all at once.
  Group 1: Q0 (project type)
  Group 2: Q1~Q4 (project definition)
  Group 3: Q5~Q8 (tech stack)
  Group 4: Q9~Q13 (infra/architecture)
  Group 5: Q14~Q16 (optional tools)
  After each group, summarize answers before next group.
  사용자가 나머지는 기본값으로라고 하면 자동 적용하고 진행.

Step 4. CODEBASE_PROFILE.md check
  → Missing: "Create codebase profile now?" confirm → execute
  → Exists: check freshness
  → New project with <3 files: defer creation

Step 5. Initialization complete report
  [Initialization Complete]
  Model: {model_name} ({effective_max:,} tokens)
  Context compression threshold: {compression_threshold:,} tokens
  Profile: {exists/missing}
  Previous context: {exists/missing}
  Ready for Q0.

### Lightweight Init (small projects)
DECISIONS.Q3 = A (small) or `initialize project --quick`:
  - Q0~Q4 only, Q5~Q8 auto-apply defaults
  - CODEBASE_PROFILE.md deferred until 3+ files exist

## Q0: Project Type
|Option|Description|
|--------|------|
|A. Greenfield|New project from scratch|
|B. Migration (same stack, version up)|Existing codebase framework/language version upgrade|
|C. Migration (language/DB swap)|Full rewrite to new stack (Re-platforming)|
|D. Migration (monolith → MSA)|Split monolith into microservices|

If B/C/D selected, all subsequent questions compare AS-IS vs TO-BE.

## Q1: Project Name & Purpose
Free text. Used as document title prefix. For migrations, also ask existing service purpose and core reason for switching.

## Q2: Expected User Scale & Traffic
|Option|Scale|Impact|
|--------|------|------|
|A. Small (≤100 concurrent)|Personal, internal tools, MVP|Single server, SQLite/PostgreSQL, caching optional|
|B. Medium (100-10,000)|Startup, early SaaS|Redis required, horizontal scaling, read replicas|
|C. Large (10,000+)|Platform, large service|CDN, sharding/clusters, message queues, orchestration|
|D. Unpredictable / bursty|Campaigns, event-driven|Serverless or auto-scaling preferred|

## Q3: Project Scale (Team & Duration)
|Option|Criteria|Strategy|
|--------|------|------|
|A. Small|1 person, ≤1 week|Minimal docs, 70% coverage, main direct push allowed, monolith|
|B. Medium|2-5 people, 1-3 months|Standard docs, 80% coverage, GitHub Flow, modular monolith|
|C. Large|6+ people, >3 months|Full docs, 90%+ coverage, GitFlow, contract tests, hexagonal|

## Q4: Expected Growth Scale
|Option|Example|Approach|
|--------|------|------|
|A. Few features (single purpose)|Event page, internal tool|Layered, test 70%, minimal docs|
|B. Continuous growth (MVP → maturity)|Startup product, commerce MVP|Modular monolith, core interfaces, test 80%, ADR|
|C. Large-scale (platform)|Large SaaS, microservice ecosystem|Hexagonal or MSA, test 90%+, full docs, ADR mandatory|

## Q5~Q8: Tech Stack
Ask after Q1~Q4. For small projects, auto-apply defaults (Python + PostgreSQL + FastAPI).
See `questions-base.prompt` in old structure for full option tables if needed.

## Q9~Q13: Infrastructure & Architecture
Ask after Q5~Q8. For small projects, auto-apply defaults.
See `questions-base.prompt` in old structure for full option tables if needed.

## Q14~Q16: Optional Tools
Multi-select. Ask after Q9~Q13. For small projects, auto-apply "none".
See `questions-base.prompt` in old structure for full option tables if needed.
